# MyTime - Windows Time Tracking App

## Project Overview
A Windows-only time tracking application built with Rust that precisely tracks users' foreground application usage. Designed for heavy users who need accurate time management data.

## Key Features
- Tracks foreground window usage exclusively
- Simple GUI with Start/Stop buttons and usage chart
- System tray integration for background operation
- CSV storage for time tracking data
- Portable Windows application

## Technical Stack
- **Language**: Rust
- **GUI Framework**: eframe/egui
- **Windows API**: windows-rs for foreground window tracking
- **Storage**: CSV files (no database in MVP)
- **Tray Icon**: tray-icon crate

## Important Notes
- This is a Windows-only application
- Must be compiled and tested on Windows environment
- Focus on simplicity for MVP
- Tracking accuracy is critical for time management

## Build Instructions
Run these commands in Windows environment:
```
cargo build --release
```

The executable will be in `target/release/mytime.exe`